<!-- PDFPage:934 --><p class="note-body">Subsec. (h)(1). <plaw congress="101" isprivate="false" number="647">Pub. L. 101–647,</plaw> §2547(a)(2), struck out after first sentence “Such hearing shall be private, unless the appropriate Federal banking agency, in its discretion, after fully considering the views of the party afforded the hearing, determines that a public hearing is necessary to protect the public interest.”</p>
