<h4 class="note-head">References in Text</h4>
<p class="note-body">Act of July 2, 1890 (the Sherman Antitrust Act), referred to in subsec. (c)(8), is classified to <uscode edition="1995" range="1 to 7" section="1" title="15">sections 1 to 7 of Title 15</uscode>, Commerce and Trade. For complete classification of the Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under <uscode edition="1995" section="1" title="15">section 1 of Title 15</uscode> and Tables.</p>
<p class="note-body">Act of October 15, 1914 (the Clayton Act), referred to in subsec. (c)(8), is act Oct. 15, 1914, ch. 323, <statuteatlarge page="730" volume="38">38 Stat. 730</statuteatlarge>, as amended, which is classified generally to <uscode edition="1995" range="12, 13, 14 to 19, 20, 21, and 22 to 27" section="12" title="15">sections 12, 13, 14 to 19, 20, 21, and 22 to 27 of Title 15</uscode>, and <uscode edition="1995" range="52 and 53" section="52" title="29">sections 52 and 53 of Title 29</uscode>, Labor. For further details and complete classification of this Act to the Code, see References in Text note set out under <uscode edition="1995" section="12" title="15">section 12 of Title 15</uscode> and Tables.</p>
<p class="note-body">The date of enactment of this subsection, referred to in subsec. (c)(10), probably means the date of enactment of <plaw congress="93" isprivate="false" number="495">Pub. L. 93–495,</plaw> which was approved Oct. 28, 1974.</p>
<p class="note-body">Section 19 of the Federal Reserve Act, as amended, referred to in subsec. (g)(1), is classified to sections 142, 371a, 371b, 371b–1, 374, 374a, 461, 463 to 466, 505, and 506 of this title. For provisions of section 19 relating to payment of interest on demand deposits, see <uscode edition="1995" section="371a" title="12">section 371a of this title</uscode>.</p>
